Audio_SamplePointer (&452C8)
#parent Audio_
=>	R0 =	data pointer
	 	0	read current data pointer
	 	>0	set data pointer to R0
	R1 =	Data length
	 	0	read current data length
	 	>0	set data length to R1
\<=	R0 =	previous data pointer
	R1 =	previous length
#line
Set data pointers to data information given.
The data for this call must be in RMA or Dynamic Area so that the player can read the data under interrupt.
